1 or l ease of goods, services, or an insurance product, insurance
2 services, or a commercial transaction in which the intended audience
3 is an actual or potential buyer or customer;
4 3. A legal action seeking recovery for bodily injury, wrongful
5 death or survival or to statements made regarding that legal action;
6 4. A legal action brought under the Oklahoma Insurance Code or
7 arising out of an insurance contract; or
8 5. A civil action brought under Section 5 of this act
9 A civil action arising from an officer-director, employee-
10 employer, or independent contractor relationship that:
11 a. seeks recovery for misappropriation of trade secrets
12 or corporate opportunities, or
13 b. seeks to enforce a non-disparagement agreement,
14 covenant not to compete, non-disclosure agreement, or
15 confidentiality agreement.
16 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
